Liquid Telecom has acquired a majority stake in Tanzania&rsquo;s internet provider Raha after getting the final regulatory approval from the Tanzania Communications Regulatory Authority. The acquisition is part of the firm&rsquo;s strategy to deepen its regional footprint through the provision of fibre optic, satellite networks and international carrier services. &ldquo;We are very pleased to announce that this transaction has received its final approval.The agreement enables Liquid Telecom to expand its footprint into Tanzania,&rdquo; Liquid Telecom chief executive Nic Rudnick said in a statement. Raha, which serves more than 1,500 businesses and retail customers, adds to Liquid Telecom&rsquo;s fibre network spanning more than 40,000 km across 12 countries.